  author: 曺係芳
  language: lzh
  text: 陽坡居士愛淸閑役役紅塵是強顔何日閉門麾俗客焚香相對說溪山
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 獻洪侍中彦博
  author: 曺係芳
  language: lzh
  text: 陽坡居士愛淸閑。役役紅塵是強顔。何日閉門麾俗客。焚香相對說溪山。
korean:
  title: 헌홍시중언박
  author: 조계방
  language: kor
  text: |-
    양파거사가 맑고 한가한 것을 사랑한다 하는데
    홍진에서 허덕이는 것은 억지로 하는 것이거니
    언제나 문을 닫고 세속 손님 사절하고
    향 사르고 마주하여 산수 이야길 할 것인가
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_0550&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Tribute to Hong Sichung Yanbok
  author: Cho Gyebang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    They say the recluse of Yang Slope loves clarity and leisure,
    Yet toiling in the dust of worldly affairs—surely forced upon him.
    When at last will he close his gate to vulgar visitors,
    And sitting across from me in incense smoke, speak of mountains and streams?
  footnotes:
    - Yang Slope (陽坡) likely refers to a retreat or residence associated with the recipient. The recluse imagery suggests an ideal of withdrawal from public life.
    - Hong Sichung (洪侍中) appears to be an official title; Yanbok may be a personal name or courtesy name of the addressee.
